Package com.cafean.vcs.utils

Class VCSystemManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.vcs.utils.VCSystemManager
  • public class VCSystemManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the static manager class for switching between version control systems in the VCS plug-in. This is where the different revision control types must be identified.

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        public static void initialize()
        Initializes the version control system manager. This will parse the plugins directory and load an instance of a VersionControlSystemDesc that should be associated with that VCS plug-in.

      • findSystem

        public static VersionControlSystemDesc findSystem​(AbstractModel model)
        Finds the version control system with the provided model. This will return null if the model is not in a version controlled directory or the model is not saved.
        Parameters:
        model - The current model controlled by a version control system
        Returns:
        The VersionControlSystemDesc that is responsible for the directory that the model is saved in.

      • findSystem

        public static VersionControlSystemDesc findSystem​(java.lang.String name)
        Finds the version control system with the provided name. This will return null if the name does not match.
        Parameters:
        name - the display name for the system.
        Returns:
        the AbstractVCSystem with the matching name.

      • getSystemNames

        public static java.util.List<VersionControlSystemDesc> getSystemNames()
        Returns the list of systems that are currently supported.
        Returns:
        A list of systems loaded by this manager.
